<TITLE> SCBA demand security for state counsels in Bangabandhu case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 26 (bdnews24.com)  The Supreme Court Bar Association Monday demanded the security for all the state counsels and lawyers involved in the appeals proceedings of the Sheikh Mujibur Rahman assassination case, after the attorney general received a death threat Monday. An anonymous letter threatened attorney general Mahbubey Alam and his family with death if convicts in the Bangabandhu murder case were not released within 15 days. SCBA president AFM Mesbah Uddin and general secretary SM Rezaul Karim in a joint statement also asked the government to track down the those who made the threat immediately and mete the severest penalty to them. They said ill efforts to intervene in the judicial process were made by threatening the attorney general. Awami League MP Sheikh Fazle Noor Taposh, also part of the state's legal team in the appeals proceedings, came under bomb attack on the night of Oct 21. bdnews
